\int_{0}^{\frac{\pi}{2}} {\frac{\cos x dx}{3 + \cos^2 x}}
\int_{0}^{\frac{\pi}{2}} {\frac{\cos x dx}{3 + \cos^2 x}} = I
\int_{0}^{\frac{\pi}{2}} {\frac{2\cos x dx}{3 + \cos^2 x}}
\int_{0}^{\frac{\pi}{2}} {\frac{\cos x dx}{3 + \cos^2 x}} = ln(3 + \cos^2 x) - I 
\rightarrow 2I = \ln(3+\cos^2 x)
\rightarrow I = \frac{\ln(3+cos^2x)}{2}, from \; 0 \; to \; \frac{\pi}{2} = \frac{ln(3) - ln(4)}{2}
\int\dfrac{2\cos x}{3+\cos^2 x}\mathrm{d}x\neq\ln(3+\cos^2x)
\dfrac{d}{dx}(3+\cos^2 x)=-2\cos x\sin x
(\neq  2\cos x)
\int\frac{\cos x}{3+\cos^2 x}\mathrm{d}x=\int\frac{\cos x}{4-\sin^2 x}\mathrm{d}x
t=\sin x
u=\sin x
